      "schema:name": "URDAIBAI Time Series",
      "schema:url": "https://www.st.nmfs.noaa.gov/copepod/time-series/es-30102/",
      "schema:description": "The Zooplankton Ecology Group of the University of the Basque Country initiated in 1997 a monitoring programme in the estuaries of Bilbao and Urdaibai (the latter also called estuary of Mundaka). Sampling is carried out monthly at the salinity sites of 35-34, 33, 30 and 26 (the last one only in Urdaibai) to obtain vertical profiles of temperature, salinity and dissolved oxygen, and to take samples for Chlorophyll a determination and zooplankton analysis. Water samples are obtained with oceanographic bottles and zooplankton samples by horizontal hauls with 200 µm plankton-nets, both at mid depth below the halocline.",
